== Quick Start Guide == 

=== How to start? ===

# Register with Kii for an Application ID and Application Key 
# Copy 1 library into your projects: KiiCloudStorageSDK-xxx.jar (java library) 
# Update the AndroidManifest.xml: 
<pre> 
<!-- permission --> 
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" /> 
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE"></uses-permission> 
<!-- the end for permission --> 
</pre> 

=== How to create an application user? === 

<pre> 
EasyClient.start(context, appName, appKey); 
KiiUser user = new KiiUser(); 
user.setEmail(email); 
user.setUsername(username); 
EasyClient.getUserManager().createUser(user, password); 
</pre> 

=== How to Log In? ===

<pre> 
EasyClient.start(context, appName, appKey); 
UserResult result = EasyClient.getUserManager().login(username, password); 
KiiUser user - result.getKiiUser(); 
</pre> 

=== How to create an object? === 

<pre> 
EasyClient.start(context, appName, appKey); 
KiiObject object = new KiiObject(); 
object.put("title", "Test"); 
object.put("body", "This is the test body"); 
EasyClient.getObjectManager().put(object); 
</pre> 

=== How to get list of objects? ===

<pre> 
EasyClient.start(context, appName, appKey); 
EntityResult result = EasyClient.getObjectManager().listAll(); 
List<KiiObject> entities = result.getEntities(KiiObject.class); 
</pre> 

== Cloud Storage Sample App ==

The purpose of this application is to provide to Android developers a simple application that allows to learn the usage of the Cloud Storage API and quickly test the operations provided. The API capabilities that can be tested are:
* User operations
** Create a user
** Login
** Logout
** Set user birthday
** Change password
** Forgot password
** Update user phone
** Show user information
* Note operations
** Create a note
** View a note
** View note list
** Refresh
** Search for a note
* File operations
** Upload a file
** List files
** View file information
** Update file information
** Download the file (get the file content)
** Delete a file
** Restore a file
** List files in trash
** Delete a file from trash
** Empty trashcan

